 door will help keep the door in operation.";i:17;s:73:"When a garage door has been poorly maintained there are noticeable signs.";i:18;s:169:"A loud screeching or banging noise when the door is opening or closing Your garage door might become very stiff and difficult to open and close The lock might get stuck.";i:19;s:84:"Spray down the garage torsion springs that lift your garage door day in and day out.";i:20;s:113:"Again you want to only lubricate them enough that they move better without a lot of extra lubricant dripping out.";i:21;s:81:"Lubricate steel hinges at their pivot points but dont mess with the plastic ones.";i:22;s:42:"Plastic doesnt need lubrication -- it can.";i:23;s:129:"Clenzoil Multi-Purpose Cleaner Lubricant Rust Prevention 3in1 Oil Bike Chain Lube Garage Door Lubricant Gun Oil and Cleaner 4 oz.";i:24;s:51:"Dropper Spray Bottle of Super Lube CLP Made in USA.";i:25;s:18:"46 out of 5 stars.";i:26;s:158:"Open the garage door and spray silicone lubricant into the centers of the rollers that ride on the track as well as on springs attached to the opening system.";i:27;s:32:"Close and open the door several.";i:28;s:37:"Tighten the garage door opener chain.";i:29;s:74:"A loose chain will make slapping sounds and cause the door to jerk around.";i:30;s:92:"Once youve completed these basic maintenance tips youre ready to lubricate your garage door.";i:31;s:48:"Step-By-Step Guide to Lubricating a Garage Door.";i:32;s:40:"Not sure how to lubricate a garage door.";i:33;s:128:"Periodic maintenance of a LiftMaster chain-driven garage door opener includes lubricating the chain and greasing the chain rail.";i:34;s:67:"As a homeowner knowing the correct type of lubricant for the chain.";i:35;s:185:"Brano Timber Door Care is an oil which is absorbed into the wood of your garage door essentially quenching the woods thirst and therefor leaving little room for the absorption of water.";i:36;s:99:"It is well-known that oil repels water which means that your door is protected against wet weather.";i:37;s:81:"Spray the overhead torsion or extension garage door springs with penetrating oil.";i:38;s:43:"Spray liberally and do not wipe off excess.";i:39;s:105:"Garage door springs are under high tension so adjustment or replacement of springs requires extreme care.";i:40;s:42:"Consider hiring a garage door maintenance.";i:41;s:146:"Lubricate the weatherstrippings every three months more frequently for high usage doors with Garaga weatherstrip lubricant or a silicon-based oil.";i:42;s:32:"Do not use petroleum-based oils.";}}